esults - Include: Delta (0.5-4Hz), Theta (4-8Hz), Alpha (8-14Hz), Beta (14-30Hz), Gamma (30-100Hz) - Important: MUST use headphones (explain why) 6. CHAPTER 3: THE COLOR SPECTRUM OF NOISE Detailed section for each: - WHITE NOISE: What it is, frequency profile, best uses, science behind it - PINK NOISE: How it differs from white, why it's better for sleep, research findings - BROWN NOISE: Deep frequencies, best for focus and blocking distractions - BLACK NOISE: Silence/near silence, meditation uses - GREEN NOISE: Nature frequency, relaxation benefits Each with a table showing: Frequency characteristics, Best for, Session length, Volume recommendations 7. CHAPTER 4: THE COMPLETE LISTENING CATALOG Create detailed tables organized by use case: TABLE 1: SLEEP & REST SOUNDS Columns: Sound Type | Frequency/Type | Duration | Method | Expected Outcome | Scientific Rationale Include 10-12 options like: - Delta binaural beats (0.5-4Hz) - Pink noise - Brown noise - 432Hz pure tone - Ocean waves - Rain sounds - Theta waves for deep REM TABLE 2: WORK & PRODUCTIVITY SOUNDS Same column structure, 8-10 options including: - Beta binaural beats (14-30Hz) - White noise - Coffee shop ambience - 40Hz gamma for focus - Brown noise for deep work TABLE 3: STUDY & LEARNING SOUNDS 8-10 options including: - Alpha binaural beats (8-14Hz) - Mozart effect frequencies - Pink noise for reading - Nature sounds TABLE 4: ANXIETY REDUCTION & CALM 8-10 options for pre-meeting/conversation anxiety: - Theta binaural beats (4-8Hz) - 528Hz (Solfeggio frequency) - Green noise - Guided breath with tones - 10-minute quick calm sessions 8. CHAPTER 5: OPTIMIZATION GUIDE - STEP-BY-STEP SOP Create a detailed table: \"Click-by-Click Setup Guide\" Columns: Step # | Action | What To Do | Expected Input | Expected Output | Why This Matters Cover: - Device setup - Headphone vs speaker decision tree - Volume calibration (explain why 30-50% is optimal) - Position/posture - Environment prep - Session timing 9. CHAPTER 6: 